== Overview == In the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Ōhesoki is noted as the father of [[Ikashikome no Mikoto]], the mother of [[Sujin Emperor]]. While his other activities are not extensively recorded in the *Nihon Shoki*, the *Sendai Kuji Hongi*'s "Tenson Honki" section recounts that in the 8th year of Emperor Kōgen's reign, Ōhesoki was appointed as Ōne, a high-Ranking ministerial position, and his brother [[Utsushikome no Mikoto]] became Ōomi (Minister). He later became Ōomi under Emperor Kaika in the 8th year of his reign.
In the {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he is identified as the grandfather of Tatetsukawa no Mikoto, indicating his importance in early genealogy.
Although the early genealogy of the Mononobe clan is somewhat inconsistent across historical sources, there is a general agreement that Ōhesoki was a fifth-generation descendant of {{ill|Nigihayahi no Mikoto|ja|饒速日命|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and a sibling to [[Utsushikome no Mikoto]]<ref>{{Cite book|author=Hoga Toshio|title=Research on Ancient Clans Vol. 8: The Mononobe Clan|publisher=Aogaki Publishing|year=2016|page=104|chapter=Four: Early Movements of the Mononobe Clan}}</ref>.
